          </timeinfo>
          <srccurr>publication date</srccurr>
        </srctime>
        <srccitea>Lovegreen 1974</srccitea>
        <srccontr>Bedrock elevation data points from cross-section</srccontr>
      </srcinfo>
      <procstep>
        <procdesc>Bedrock elevation data from historical and recent boreholes, wells, outcrops, and seismic surveys were compiled into a point shapefile in ArcGIS Pro. Point elevation data represent a mix of publicly available data with references provided, and proprietary data for which references are unavailable for security concerns.  A bedrock elevation raster was generated from the point data set by interpolating bedrock elevation using the Topo to Raster toolbox, and 100-ft contours were generated from the raster using spatial analyst tools. Depth to bedrock data were acquired by subtracting the bedrock elevation from the surface elevation at each data point, and interpolating the the depth to bedrock using the Topo to Raster toolbox.</procdesc>
        <procdate>2021</procdate>
      </procstep>
